[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

You open with a Weak 2-Bid, 2\D. Partner responds 2NT. What do you say next? 

The 2NT bid is forcing and your suit is A K Q x x x. This is the standard guideline where you must rebid 3NT. When you do, partner passes. Nice.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:KQ9763.J2.J6.754 J.Q9854.874.AT62 A854.3.AK52.KQ83 T2.AKT76.QT93.J9"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "2b2b71713f6c46c8d26b72293bdc736bc68ac68346c13e20de3411a66ca82b62"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/weak_2s"]
[Student "S"]
{You should raise to 4\S because that is what you expect partner to make. }

